1. Problem Statement: Fragmented Cross-Border Asset Management

Context: High-net-worth individuals and institutional investors often hold diverse portfolios comprising traditional and alternative assets across multiple jurisdictions. Managing these assets involves navigating various regulatory frameworks, dealing with different custodians, and facing challenges in achieving a consolidated view of their holdings. 

Challenges:
	‚Ä¢	Regulatory Compliance: Each jurisdiction has its own set of regulations, making compliance complex and time-consuming.
	‚Ä¢	Lack of Interoperability: Traditional financial systems are siloed, hindering seamless asset transfers and consolidated reporting.
	‚Ä¢	Operational Inefficiencies: Manual processes and intermediaries increase the cost and time required for asset management.
	‚Ä¢	Limited Transparency: Investors lack real-time visibility into their diversified portfolios, affecting decision-making.

‚∏ª

